# S05-T07: Accept Epic → PLANNER Write-Back (protocol-critical)

## Objective
Accepting an epic makes PLANNER decompose it AND write LOCKED Totem files (invariant §3).

## Execution
- `POST /api/epics/[id]/accept`:
  1. Mock PLANNER decomposes the epic into 3–6 tasks (title, lead_role, position).
  2. Create a board + `wc_tasks` rows (status `todo`, `epic_id` set).
  3. **Write `.ptl` + one `.pd` per task** into the instance `sprints/`, all `gate: LOCKED`,
     next free `S<NN>` id, matching house format (frontmatter + Objective/Tasks/DoD).
     Store each `.pd` filename back on its `wc_tasks.totem_pd_file`.
  4. Mark epic `accepted`; emit `epic.accepted` + `board.created` (T09).
- HARD RULE: write ONLY under `sprints/`; never auto-set `gate: OPEN` (invariant §4/§5).

## Out
`POST /api/epics/[id]/accept`, `server/utils/totem-writer.ts`

## Done when
- Accept yields a board AND new `gate: LOCKED` `.ptl`/`.pd` files; no gate auto-opened.
